      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted NIH must agree with experimental comparator within 25% across at least three operating points; worst-case operating point must be correctly identified.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted NIH values are compared against the VAD steady-flow hemolysis benchmark dataset (ASTM F1841 protocol, bovine blood, Hct 33%). Agreement is within 18% across four overlapping operating points. The worst-case operating point (highest flow, highest speed) is correctly ranked by the model. The benchmark is described as representative of the hydraulic regime relevant to centrifugal blood pumps in this specific-speed range. The assessment does not address whether pulsatile CPB inflow conditions would alter the hemolysis distribution or the ranking of worst-case operating points relative to the steady-flow comparator used here."
    },
    {
