    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors are scoped out as not required at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. The CFD model is assessed as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under CPB conditions. Validation evidence from the VAD steady-flow benchmark demonstrates NIH prediction accuracy within 18% of experimental measurements, and worst-case operating point ranking is correctly reproduced. The credibility assessment team accepts the model for use in the declared COU.",
